WordPress-DBIC-Schema

This is a basic schema (and mostly a work in progress) for the
WordPress database, which can be used for migrations, data fetching
etc.

It comes with some relationships even if the DB doesn't implement them
with foreign keys.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc WordPress::DBIC::Schema

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        https://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=WordPress-DBIC-Schema

